name: Mustafa Kemal Ataturk
description: Mustafa Kemal Atatürk. Turkish field marshal, revolutionary statesman, author, and the founding father of the Republic of  Turkey.He undertook sweeping progressive reforms, which modernized Turkey into a secular, industrial nation. Ideologically a secularist and nationalist, his policies and theories became known as Kemalism. Due to his military and political accomplishments, Atatürk is regarded as one of the most important political leaders of the 20th century.
